article.headline: Colorado 71, Texas Tech 68
article.story: LUBBOCK, Texas -- Levi Knutson scored 18 points to lead Colorado over Texas Tech 71-68 on Wednesday night. The Buffaloes (17-11, 6-7 Big 12) led most of the way and survived a 21-5 surge by the Red Raiders early in the second half. Texas Tech (12-16, 4-9) went up briefly late in the game, 63-62, on a layup by D'walyn Roberts but couldn't sustain its momentum. Knutson hit the second of two free throw with 15.3 seconds remaining to seal the win. A desperation shot by David Tairu missed its mark to end the game. The Buffaloes, who got just their third road win of the season, outrebounded the Red Raiders 40-34. Marcus Relphorde added 15 points for Colorado. John Roberson scored 18 points, and Mike Singletary added 17 to lead Texas Tech.
